    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-08-31T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-08-31T16:00:00-05:00" n="292"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d292">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">600.329/8–2548: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in Brazil</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-08-31T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >August 31, 1948—5 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>646. Dept greatly concerned reported prohibition exports canned meat reported
                        <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 955, Aug 25.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d292fn1">Not printed.</note> Wilson and Co, Chicago, advised that on
                    basis Carteira position described <gloss target="#t_Embtel1">Embtel</gloss> 905,
                    Aug 13,<note n="1" xml:id="d292fn2">Not printed.</note> has firm commitment for
                    650,000 lb. canned beef and request to offer 2,640,000 lb. additional from US
                    Army Quartermaster, all for shipment to Greece arrival not later than Oct.</p>
                <p>Dept fully appreciative difficulties facing Braz Govt in allowing these exports
                    in face further rationing restrictions. <gloss target="#t_Emb1">Emb</gloss>
                    requested follow matter closely and reemphasize, if opportunity presents itself,
                    these stocks canned beef reportedly unmarketable in Brazil urgently needed
                    Europe. Advise Dept soonest if Finance Min requested reconsideration <pb
                        facs="0420" n="404" xml:id="pg_404"/> reported new prohibition<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d292fn3">In telegram 987, September 3, 4 p. m., not printed, the
                        Embassy reported that the prohibition was lifted (600.329/9–348).</note>
                    against exports and results these representations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Marshall</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
